ls - ls is the list command in linux. This command is used to show the contents of your directory.
     Syntax - ls
     
Following are the commands related to ls which are as follows :-

1) To show the list of all directories including hidden files :
   Syntax - ls -a
   
2) To display files in a long list format :
   Syntax - ls -l
   
3) To display only sub-directories exclding all files :
   Syntax - ls -d*/
   
4) To display the file size in terms of Mb,Gb,etc :
   Syntax - ls -lh
   
5) To display files in descending order according to file size :
   Syntax - ls -lhs
   
6) To display only group ID and owner ID :
   Syntax - ls -n
   
7) To display the list in reverse order :
   Syntax - ls -r
   
8) To display the contents of home directory :
   Syntax - ls ~
   
9) To display the contents of parent directory :
   Syntax - ls../
   
10) To check the version of ls command :
    Syntax - ls --version
   

